snippet.textDisplay:
There's a lot of mistrust of CCP covid death statistics. Many are very doubtful that the initial zero covid policy was actually more effective at preventing spread.

I remember hearing that some Chinese netizens noticed a massive out of the norm decrease (in the millions) of cell phone subscribers (or some similar service) and it was speculated that it was an indication of the death count.
